    "LSAT), where higher scores are taken into account for admission into select institutions (US News and World Report 2022).",
    "Setting these objections aside, however, to the extent that one believes the UBE to be a valid proxy for lawyerly competence, these results suggest GPT-4 to be substantially less lawyerly competent than previously assumed, as GPT-4's score against likely attorneys (i.e.",
    "those who actually passed the bar) is ∼48th percentile.",
    "Moreover, when just looking at the essays, which more closely resemble the tasks of practicing lawyers and thus more plausibly reflect lawyerly competence, GPT-4's performance falls in the bottom ∼15th percentile.",
    "These findings align with recent research work finding that GPT-4 performed below-average on law school exams (Blair-Stanek et al. 2023)."
